    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but calling a doctor or going to the er feels like such an overreaction when he's literally just sitting here resting. he's even saying he's fine now. isn't it pretty common for people to have weird sensations after sitting in cramped economy seats for 12 hours? like maybe it's just some temporary nerve compression or something? i'd rather just let him sleep and see if he's back to normal in the morning instead of causing a whole scene.",
